Spanish PM forced out of office Maria and Consolata, who were against the idea of being surgically separated, also told the BBC that they hoped to get married to one husband someday. The two, whose parents died while they were still infants, were raised by the Catholic charity Maria Consolata, which had adopted and named them. Last year, their high school graduation triggered a wave of congratulatory messages nationwide.